<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Judge Temporarily Pauses Paramount-Warner Bros. Deal</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/business/media/paramount-warner-bros-deal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/business/media/paramount-warner-bros-deal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/business/media/paramount-warner-bros-deal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The delay is intended to give the court time to consider a lawsuit that argues the $111 billion merger violates antitrust laws.</description><dc:creator>David McCabe</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2026 17:23:59 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Paramount Pictures</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mergers and Acquisitions</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Paramount Skydance</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Warner Bros. Discovery</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Competition law</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rob Bonta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Attorney general</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Movies</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">California</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/20/multimedia/20biz-paramount-cgbh/20biz-paramount-cgbh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mark Abramson for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The Warner Bros. studio in Burbank, Calif.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>How Google’s A.I. Search Is Imperiling the Open Web</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/google-ai-open-web.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/google-ai-open-web.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/google-ai-open-web.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>As Google incorporates more artificial intelligence into search, people are spending more time on Google. Some website operators are crying foul.</description><dc:creator>Kate Conger</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2026 14:04:16 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Search Engines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">TheVerge.com</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Wikipedia</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/07/business/00google-web-image/00google-web-image-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600-v2.jpg" medium="image" /></item><item><title>Tesla Profit Falls Even as Car Sales Rebound</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/business/tesla-earnings-elon-musk.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/business/tesla-earnings-elon-musk.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/business/tesla-earnings-elon-musk.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company is selling more cars, but the company’s profit was down because of price cuts and higher expenses.</description><dc:creator>Jack Ewing</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:15:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Earnings Reports</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Driverless Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Self-Driving Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Service</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Taxis</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Stocks</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Bonds</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">GM</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Waymo</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Europe</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/22/multimedia/22BIZ-TESLA-01-vkfp/22BIZ-TESLA-01-vkfp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Eduardo Munoz/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Car sales account for more than 70 percent of Tesla’s revenue, but investors are more focused on the company’s efforts to develop self-driving taxis and robots with humanlike form. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>What Happened When Meta Used A.I. to Ban Accounts on Facebook and Instagram</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/meta-ai-facebook-instagram-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/meta-ai-facebook-instagram-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/meta-ai-facebook-instagram-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Users said the technology mistakenly deleted their accounts. To resolve the issue, they still had to rely on A.I.</description><dc:creator>Stuart A. Thompson and Eli Tan</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 15:31:11 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Instagram</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Customer service</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/07/multimedia/META-AI-1-06-jgcb/META-AI-1-06-jgcb-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Daniel Rodrigues for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Alphabet Quadruples Profit to $112 Billion, Fueled by A.I. Investments</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/alphabet-google-earnings-profit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/alphabet-google-earnings-profit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/alphabet-google-earnings-profit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Google’s parent company, which has spent heavily on artificial intelligence, also showed growth across its businesses, particularly in cloud computing.</description><dc:creator>Kate Conger</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:42:37 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cloud computing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Search Engines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Earnings Reports</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/22/multimedia/22biz-google-earnings-qpgz/22biz-google-earnings-qpgz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Lucia Vazquez for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>A Times Square ad for Google, which reported its financial results on Wednesday.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Lawsuit Against Meta Over Social Media Addiction Is Dropped</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/meta-social-media-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/meta-social-media-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/22/technology/meta-social-media-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>For Meta, the move was a reprieve after it and YouTube were found guilty in another case in March of negligence and personal injury for their platforms’ addictive features.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan and Cecilia Kang</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 18:29:02 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Addiction</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Product liability</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Consumer protection</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Legislation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Compensatory Damages</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Victim Compensation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Teens</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Instagram</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">TikTok</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">YouTube</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/22/multimedia/22biz-meta-lawsuit-fmkh/22biz-meta-lawsuit-fmkh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Stella Kalinina for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The dismissal follows Meta’s loss in March in the same court against a now 20-year-old California woman who accused the company and YouTube of negligence and personal injury for their addictive features.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Why Silicon Valley Can’t Stop Looking Over Its Shoulder at China</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/china-us-ai-race.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/china-us-ai-race.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/20/technology/china-us-ai-race.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Chinese companies are offering artificial intelligence that is nearly as good as the leading U.S. technologies, but it’s still America’s race to lose.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2026 09:02:12 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Moonshot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenRouter</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Xi Jinping</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/17/multimedia/00biz-us-china-ai-xi-qcwh/00biz-us-china-ai-xi-qcwh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Greg Baker/Agence France-Presse — Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>On Friday, China’s leader, Xi Jinping, hailed Beijing as the champion of a new global A.I. order.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>The Yoto Music Box Is a Ray of Hope Amid the ‘Techlash’</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Amid widespread “techlash” over addictive screens and apps, the Yoto, an audio player for children, shows there’s still a way to make money while doing something nice.</description><dc:creator>Brian X. Chen and Sam Bush</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 09:01:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electronics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Audio Recordings</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Downloads and Streaming</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Music</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Yoto</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">The Beatles</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/23/23visualUploader-33452-cover/23visualUploader-33452-cover-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600-v2.jpg" medium="image" /></item></channel></rss>